#jnVaga
Release manager
Responsibilities 
·Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing a product release process that follows industry standards and best practices. The goal is to ensure that product releases are delivered on time and with high quality to ensure continued customer satisfaction. This will involve coordinating activities during the release planning stage, monitoring and controlling the release plan during the development and testing stage, and coordinating product launch.
·Responsible for ensuring there is a full suite of regression test procedures, test equipment, and test data for all functional and non-functional requirements. This will involve working closely with the organization (Development, Quality Assurance, Project Delivery, Customer Support, etc.) to ensure the regression test procedures are comprehensive, up-to-date, and effective. The regression test procedures must follow industry standards and best practices.
· Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing test automation to improve the efficiency of the release process while increasing test coverage and minimizing defect leakage. This will involve working closely with the Development team to prioritize functional areas that are good candidates for test automation, and managing the implementation of test automation tools and procedures.
· Responsible for supporting and following up AGILE delivery routines and procedures

Expected skills and qualifications:
·  Bachelor in Computer Science or related field.
·   Knowledge of industry standards for software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience in software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience implementing test automation is required.
·  Experience with Jira and Confluence is preferred.
·   Strong organizational skills are required.
·   Excellent communication (verbal and written) is required.
·   Ability to work independently to achieve operational goals.
·   Strong knowledgement of CDIC and devops automation
·   Knowledgement of code release strategy, branching and build cycles
·   Ability to understand the system dependencies and component dependencies and plan accordingly
·   Plus for SCRUM certification

Skills
Excellent communications skills
Candidate has to be fluent in English and Portuguese as this is a multi geography project with teams in Brazil/US/India

Lead Development

Responsibilities 
·    Leadership position that exercises people influence without the responsibility of people management, and focuses on technical project management, translating business requirements into software, in addition to hands-on delivery
·    Run team meetings effectively, balance their technical project management tasks with writing code, work with their team on removing technical obstacles, and facilitate mentoring of other developers.
·    Report to the program manager or portfolio manager like the rest of their team, but will work in close collaboration with the manager in order to scale the work across multiple teams and projects.
·    Actively contribute to sprint planning and ceremonies and will actively pursue simpler technical approaches, or justify technical complexity when required.

Expected skills and qualifications:
·     Senior Developer with a solid grasp of system architecture of services under the team’s area of ownership
·     Clear communication skills, both verbal and written
·     Proficiency with system design and architecture
·     Strong understanding of software development best practices
·     Experience leading cross-functional teams and sprint ceremonies in an agile scrum environment
·     Experience working in a high-growth product startup
·     Experience managing technical disagreement and decision making
·     Previous mentorship over junior developers
·     Strong knowledge in JAVA, node JS, typescript
·     Strong knowledge in FULL Stack development
·     Strong knowledge in working with databases such as mongoDB,
·     Strong knowledge in microservices architecture and restful APIs

Skills
Excellent communications skills
Candidate has to be fluent in English and Portuguese as this is a multi geography project with teams in Brazil/US/India

Lead SIT Tester:
Responsibilities:
Review integration system/software/module requirements and design/prepare test scenarios.
Execute tests system/software/module integration.
Verify if the integration has any impact on other systems/software/modules’ coexistence by performing individual and then combined tests.
Analyse test results on database or modules impacts, errors or bugs, and connection/integration.
Prepare reports on all aspects related to the system/software/module testing carried out and reporting to the design team.
Interact with clients/SMEs/BAs/BSAs to understand integration requirements.
Participate in design reviews and provide input on requirements, integration design, and potential problems.

Experience:
Minimum five years of experience in system integration testing is required (minimum two years leading and designing tests)
Up-to-date knowledge of software test design and testing methodologies.
Working knowledge of test techniques and compatibility with various software programs.
Working knowledge of programming.
Excellent communication and critical thinking skills.
Good organizational skills and detail-oriented mindset.
Experience with Jira/Confluence is preferred.

Skills:
Fluent in English and Portuguese as this is a multi-geography project with teams in Brazil/US/India (mandatory)

Release manager
Responsibilities 
·Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing a product release process that follows industry standards and best practices. The goal is to ensure that product releases are delivered on time and with high quality to ensure continued customer satisfaction. This will involve coordinating activities during the release planning stage, monitoring and controlling the release plan during the development and testing stage, and coordinating product launch.
·Responsible for ensuring there is a full suite of regression test procedures, test equipment, and test data for all functional and non-functional requirements. This will involve working closely with the organization (Development, Quality Assurance, Project Delivery, Customer Support, etc.) to ensure the regression test procedures are comprehensive, up-to-date, and effective. The regression test procedures must follow industry standards and best practices.
· Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing test automation to improve the efficiency of the release process while increasing test coverage and minimizing defect leakage. This will involve working closely with the Development team to prioritize functional areas that are good candidates for test automation, and managing the implementation of test automation tools and procedures.
· Responsible for supporting and following up AGILE delivery routines and procedures

Expected skills and qualifications:
·  Bachelor in Computer Science or related field.
·   Knowledge of industry standards for software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience in software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience implementing test automation is required.
·  Experience with Jira and Confluence is preferred.
·   Strong organizational skills are required.
·   Excellent communication (verbal and written) is required.
·   Ability to work independently to achieve operational goals.
·   Strong knowledgement of CDIC and devops automation
·   Knowledgement of code release strategy, branching and build cycles
·   Ability to understand the system dependencies and component dependencies and plan accordingly
·   Plus for SCRUM certification

Skills
Excellent communications skills
Candidate has to be fluent in English and Portuguese as this is a multi geography project with teams in Brazil/US/India

#jnVaga
Release manager
Responsibilities 
·Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing a product release process that follows industry standards and best practices. The goal is to ensure that product releases are delivered on time and with high quality to ensure continued customer satisfaction. This will involve coordinating activities during the release planning stage, monitoring and controlling the release plan during the development and testing stage, and coordinating product launch.
·Responsible for ensuring there is a full suite of regression test procedures, test equipment, and test data for all functional and non-functional requirements. This will involve working closely with the organization (Development, Quality Assurance, Project Delivery, Customer Support, etc.) to ensure the regression test procedures are comprehensive, up-to-date, and effective. The regression test procedures must follow industry standards and best practices.
· Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing test automation to improve the efficiency of the release process while increasing test coverage and minimizing defect leakage. This will involve working closely with the Development team to prioritize functional areas that are good candidates for test automation, and managing the implementation of test automation tools and procedures.
· Responsible for supporting and following up AGILE delivery routines and procedures

Expected skills and qualifications:
·  Bachelor in Computer Science or related field.
·   Knowledge of industry standards for software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience in software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience implementing test automation is required.
·  Experience with Jira and Confluence is preferred.
·   Strong organizational skills are required.
·   Excellent communication (verbal and written) is required.
·   Ability to work independently to achieve operational goals.
·   Strong knowledgement of CDIC and devops automation
·   Knowledgement of code release strategy, branching and build cycles
·   Ability to understand the system dependencies and component dependencies and plan accordingly
·   Plus for SCRUM certification

Skills
Excellent communications skills
Candidate has to be fluent in English and Portuguese as this is a multi geography project with teams in Brazil/US/India

Release manager
Responsibilities 
·Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing a product release process that follows industry standards and best practices. The goal is to ensure that product releases are delivered on time and with high quality to ensure continued customer satisfaction. This will involve coordinating activities during the release planning stage, monitoring and controlling the release plan during the development and testing stage, and coordinating product launch.
·Responsible for ensuring there is a full suite of regression test procedures, test equipment, and test data for all functional and non-functional requirements. This will involve working closely with the organization (Development, Quality Assurance, Project Delivery, Customer Support, etc.) to ensure the regression test procedures are comprehensive, up-to-date, and effective. The regression test procedures must follow industry standards and best practices.
· Responsible for defining, implementing, and managing test automation to improve the efficiency of the release process while increasing test coverage and minimizing defect leakage. This will involve working closely with the Development team to prioritize functional areas that are good candidates for test automation, and managing the implementation of test automation tools and procedures.
· Responsible for supporting and following up AGILE delivery routines and procedures

Expected skills and qualifications:
·  Bachelor in Computer Science or related field.
·   Knowledge of industry standards for software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience in software quality assurance is required.
·   Minimum five years of experience implementing test automation is required.
·  Experience with Jira and Confluence is preferred.
·   Strong organizational skills are required.
·   Excellent communication (verbal and written) is required.
·   Ability to work independently to achieve operational goals.
·   Strong knowledgement of CDIC and devops automation
·   Knowledgement of code release strategy, branching and build cycles
·   Ability to understand the system dependencies and component dependencies and plan accordingly
·   Plus for SCRUM certification

Skills
Excellent communications skills
Candidate has to be fluent in English and Portuguese as this is a multi geography project with teams in Brazil/US/India

Gerente de Tecnologia da Informação

Local de trabalho: on site: Cascavel-PR
Email para envio de currículo: selecao@wehunt.com.br

RESPONSABILIDADES:
• Fazer o gerenciamento de projetos de desenvolvimento de tecnologia, bem como gerir equipe de desenvolvedores internos com aproximadamente 15 pessoas (presencial e remoto);
• Desenvolver soluções web, infraestrutura e principalmente cloud;
• Realizar gerenciamento de projetos com metodologias ágeis;
• Criação, implantação e acompanhamento dos indicadores de gestão da área;
• Identificar as melhores práticas utilizadas no mercado, de acordo com o nosso modelo de negócio;
• Negociar contratos pertinentes à área;
• Planejar e implementar políticas de backup e planos de contingência de acordo com um planejamento conjunto entre TI e direção da empresa;
• Elaborar o planejamento orçamentário da área, identificando todas as necessidades de curto, médio e longo prazo;
• Planejar todas as demais ações do setor, assim como políticas internas, visando mitigar a quebra da segurança lógica e física da estrutura de informações da empresa;
• Discutir os requerimentos do negócio e antecipar-se aos possíveis riscos.

PRÉ-REQUISITOS:
• Graduação em ciências da computação, engenharia, sistemas ou cursos correlatos à tecnologia da informação;
• Experiência prévia com gestão de times de desenvolvimento de software/ Squads;
• Experiência com integração de sistemas internos como ERP, CRM, logística, etc.;
• Conhecimento em arquitetura de software web;
• Experiência com metodologias ágeis;
• Conhecimento em infraestrutura de alta complexidade, principalmente em cloud AWS.

DIFERENCIAIS:

• Ter atuado com a criação e implantação de squads;
• Ter atuado como Líder técnico, Product Owner (PO), DevOps e/ou Especialista de Negócios TI;
• Conhecimento em linguagens de programação Ruby e/ou Python.


COMPETÊNCIAS TÉCNICAS:
• Conhecer o mercado e o nosso negócio, para propor soluções pertinentes ao nosso produto;
• Ter visão estratégica de área, produto e negócios. Maior parte de nossas aplicações e produtos passam pelo TI;
• Conhecimento em linguagem de programação avançada;
• Visão de Negócios (curto, médio e longo prazo);
• Aplicação, desenvolvimento e acompanhamento de indicadores estratégicos de área;
• Desenho e controle do plano orçamentário da área (hoje a maior em termos de Capex);
• Orientação a dados.
